International - An Indian American doctor couple has pledged $200million (R2.6 billion) to a Florida university to advance healthcare in the state and internationally to under-served communities in India and Africa. Zambia-born cardiologist Dr Kiran C Patel and his wife, paediatrician Dr Pallavi Patel announced the largest donation made by an Indian American individual or family in the US at a press event in Fort Lauderdale on Monday. “Over the next 20 years, NSU will train thousands of new doctors and other health care professionals who will directly touch millions of lives,” said Dr Pallavi Patel.